news.title: Dubai property prices higher but rents continue to fall: CBRE
news.para: An ongoing fall in rents signalled continued weakness in the long-troubled sector. Dubai rents continued to trend lower, falling by 2.7% on average in the year ending in August, CBRE said in a report.

news.title: Fall in China's $1.3 trillion land sales to test local finances, economy
news.para: Land sales soared to a record 8.4 trillion yuan ($1.3 trillion) in 2020, the equivalent of Australia's annual gross domestic product, bolstering fiscal budgets in a pandemic year.

news.title: Evictions begin as US ban ends, but not the spike feared
news.para: After a slow start, the pace to distribute the first $25 billion installment of $46.5 billion in rental assistance is picking up. Treasury Department officials said the program had served 420,000 households in August - up from 340,000 in July - and distributed $7.7 billion since January.

news.title: Macrotech Developers sales bookings jump 88% to Rs 2,003 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Abhishek Lodha, MD and CEO of Macrotech Developers, said, "Led by the strength of our brand and resilient industry trends, we have shown strong pre-sales growth of 88 per cent during the quarter on a y-o-y (year-on-year) basis and more than doubled our pre-sales on a q-o-q (quarter-on-quarter) basis."

news.title: Action taken against 2,500 buildings: Ahmedabad civic body
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) informed the Gujarat high court on Wednesday that it has undertaken an exhaustive and vigorous drive to ensure that the fire safety norms are properly adhered to and the buildings obtain valid fire NOC

news.title: HC ban order may hit plan to regularise land in Rajasthan
news.para: As per rules, regularisation can only be done in cities with a population of over 1 lakh after implementing the zonal development plan. Out of 29 big cities, the zonal plans have only been put in place in some cities, including Jaipur and Jodhpur.

news.title: Jaisalmer: HC bars construction around Sonar Fort during land deed campaign
news.para: The Centre included Jaisalmer’s Sonar, Chittorgarh, Ranthambhore, Amber, Gagron and Kumbhalgarh forts in the list of official hill forts of Rajasthan in 2011 and later in 2013, the UNESCO included the forts in the list of world heritage sites.

news.title: Coimbatore airport expansion: Property owners stage protest
news.para: The protesters said there were 110 houses in parcel of land proposed for acquisition. Considering the number of owners of the vacant land who have come forward to give their land, they are minuscule in number.

news.title: Construction waste from sites to be disposed at C&D plant only: EDMC
news.para: The owners or builders undertaking work related to construction or renovation at sites will have to dispose construction and demolition waste only at Shastri Park C&D waste processing plant, East Delhi Mayor Shyam Sunder Aggarwal said.

news.title: SVAMITVA Yojana gave boost to rural economy: Prime Minister
news.para: The scheme aims at establishment of clear ownership of property in rural areas by mapping of land parcels using drone technology and providing 'record of rights' to eligible households by issuing legal ownership cards to them.

news.title: SAP India renews lease for one lakh sq ft office in Vatika Towers in Gurugram
news.para: SAP has been operating in VatikaTowers for over 14 years and has extended its lease for a new term of nine years. “We can confirm that the company has extended their lease,” said Ritu Gupta, head-leasing, Vatika Ltd.

news.title: Gujarat CM promises administrative reforms for real estate sector
news.para: “The state government is ready to take up administrative reforms. Whatever reforms are required for the building sector will be undertaken in consultation with the industry,” Bhupendra Patel said.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance exits OakNorth Holdings for Rs 3,049 crore
news.para: In November 2015, Indiabulls Housing Finance acquired a 39.76 per cent stake in OakNorth Holdings Limited for Rs 663 crore (USD 100 million), the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Ambience case: Court pulls up Tihar authorities for discriminating between inmates
news.para: The central probe agency had raided Gehlot, his company Aman Hospitality Private Limited (AHPL), some other firms of the Ambience group, director in the company Dayanand Singh, Mohan Singh Gehlot, and their associates in July last year.

news.title: Noida authority hopes to demolish Supertech twin towers before Nov 30
news.para: Additional CEO Neha Sharma said, “We are hopeful of demolishing the twin towers before November 30. CBRI has told us that Indian companies have the expertise of handling the demolition exercise. Tenders will be floated soon to find a suitable agency.”
